synthesis_method: The electrolyte synthesis process involved two stages: 1) High-energy ball milling of lithium, phosphoric sulfide, lithium-tin alloy powder, and Cosan in a specific molar ratio in a planetary ball mill for 5 hours to create a Lithium sulfur phosphor tin mixture, and 2) Secondary high-energy ball milling with added silver iodide and silver chlorate in a glove box under argon gas for 36 hours to obtain an amorphous li sulfur phosphor tin mixture containing the silver compounds.
